records.nl_statement: Suppose $f^{\prime}(x)>0$ in $(a, b)$. Prove that $f$ is strictly increasing in $(a, b)$, and let $g$ be its inverse function. Prove that $g$ is differentiable, and that $g^{\prime}(f(x))=\frac{1}{f^{\prime}(x)} \quad(a<x<b)$.

  DifferentiableOn ℝ g (Set.Ioo a b) ∧
  ∀ x ∈ Set.Ioo a b, deriv g (f x) = 1 / deriv f x :=
